  "title": "Procurement Executive (F&B)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Overview:</strong></p>\n<p>The Procurement Executive is responsible for supporting the Procurement Manager in carrying out the day-to-day procurement activities and all procurement execution for the company.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Support Procurement Manager in all matters relating to purchasing, which includes but not limited to stock monitoring, stock replenishment, quality control, handling disputes e.g. quantity differences, damaged or expired products).</li>\n  <li>Perform vendor screening, supply market research and analytical studies to identify and select potential suppliers to be added to the pre-approved vendor list.</li>\n  <li>Review and evaluate quotations from vendor.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate purchasing activities and services based on company’s needs.</li>\n  <li>Monitor process and supplier performance and resolve issues with suppliers.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with restaurant teams on requirements and provide support on delivery issues</li>\n  <li>Monitor contracts and renewal prior to expiry</li>\n  <li>Any other ad hoc duties as assigned by the manager.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of relevant procurement experience within the F&amp;B industry.</li>\n  <li>Good track record in the areas of cost management, vendor management, quality controls and inventory management</li>\n  <li>Positive work attitude, proactive, resourceful and independent</li>\n  <li>Organized and meticulous</li>\n</ul>",
